<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE suite SYSTEM "http://testng.org/testng-1.0.dtd">
<suite name="ogcapi-connectedsystems10-${version}" verbose="0" configfailurepolicy="continue">
  <parameter name="iut"  value=""/>
  <parameter name="ics"  value=""/>
  <parameter name="mutation-tests-enabled"  value=""/>
  <parameter name="mutation-iut-policy"  value=""/>

  <listeners>
    <listener class-name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.listener.TestRunListener" />
    <listener class-name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.listener.SuiteFixtureListener" />
    <listener class-name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.listener.TestFailureListener" />
  </listeners>

  <!-- Single <test> block hosts Core, SystemFeatures, AND Common classes so TestNG's
       group-dependency mechanism resolves group "core" within the same scope as
       the "systemfeatures" group (group dependencies are <test>-scoped — methods
       in different <test> blocks cannot reference each other's groups, per
       TestNG-1.0.dtd semantics; verified empirically via DependencyMap "depends
       on nonexistent group" error when split across blocks).

       Group "systemfeatures" depends-on "core" so all systemfeatures-tagged
       @Tests SKIP gracefully if any core-tagged @Test FAILs (closes
       SCENARIO-ETS-PART1-002-SYSTEMFEATURES-DEPENDENCY-SKIP-001 per design.md
       §"SystemFeatures conformance class scope" snippet).

       Group "common" is INDEPENDENT of Core (same group-dependency-DAG-root level
       — see architect-handoff S-ETS-03-07 readiness rationale + Sprint 3 contract
       acceptance criterion). Common runs in parallel with Core; the load-bearing
       Common assertions are at the JSON-encoding-class layer + Common Part 2
       collections layer which Core does NOT cover (Core asserts the
       landing-page+oas30 SUCCESS-side sub-requirements only). Sprint 4+ may
       reconsider when 4+ classes need the BeforeSuite SkipException pattern noted
       in Sprint 2 inline comment.

       <run> block has no <include>/<exclude> filter so all groups run; the
       dependency map handles ordering and skip semantics.
       Core tests stay in group "core"; SystemFeatures tests stay in group
       "systemfeatures"; Common tests stay in group "common". -->
  <!-- Sprint 4 S-ETS-04-05 (REQ-ETS-PART1-003): Subsystems group added; FIRST
       two-level dependency chain in this ETS (Subsystems → SystemFeatures → Core).
       Per ADR-010 v2 amendment (Architect 2026-04-29) defense-in-depth: the
       <group depends-on> declaration here is the structural cascade; a
       @BeforeClass SkipException fallback in SubsystemsTests.fetchSubsystemsCollection
       cascades all 4 @Tests to SKIP if (a) IUT attribute missing, (b) no parent
       system has subsystems, or (c) /subsystems returns non-200. This mitigates
       Architect-surfaced risk TESTNG-BEFORE-SUITE-VS-DEPENDS-ON-GROUPS-INTERACTION-
       ORDERING (TestNG 7.9.0 transitive cascade behavior is undocumented; the
       @BeforeClass fallback is conditionally inert if cascade works as expected,
       load-bearing if not). -->
  <!-- Sprint 5 S-ETS-05-05 (REQ-ETS-PART1-006) + S-ETS-05-06 (REQ-ETS-PART1-004):
       Procedures and Deployments groups added; both depend on SystemFeatures via
       the now-VERIFIED-LIVE TestNG 7.9.0 transitive cascade (ADR-010 v3 amendment
       2026-04-29 — Sprint 4 Raze sabotage exec total=26/passed=16/failed=1/skipped=9
       confirms two-level cascade fires end-to-end). Mechanical pattern extension of
       Subsystems Sprint 4 baseline: same single-block consolidation, same
       <group depends-on="systemfeatures"/> declaration, same @BeforeClass
       SkipException fallback in each new class (defense-in-depth retained as
       inert insurance per Sprint 4 live verification). -->
  <!-- Sprint 7 S-ETS-07-02 (REQ-ETS-PART1-007) + S-ETS-07-03 (REQ-ETS-PART1-008):
       SamplingFeatures and PropertyDefinitions groups added; both depend on
       SystemFeatures via the same cascade pattern. Sprint 7 S-ETS-07-01 Wedge 1
       (REQ-ETS-CLEANUP-018) closed the 2-sprint-old sabotage-marker javac defect;
       cascade XML at ops/test-results/sprint-ets-07-01-wedge1-sabotage-cascade-
       2026-04-30.xml retroactively VERIFIES the 3-class cascade (Subsystems +
       Procedures + Deployments) — adding SamplingFeatures + PropertyDefinitions
       extends the cascade to 5 sibling classes at the SystemFeatures level. -->
  <!-- Sprint 8 S-ETS-08-02 (REQ-ETS-PART1-005): Subdeployments group added; FIRST
       three-deep dependency chain in this ETS (Subdeployments to Deployments to
       SystemFeatures to Core). Subdeployments depends-on="deployments" (NOT
       "systemfeatures"); the cascade is transitive — when SystemFeatures is
       sabotaged, Deployments cascade-SKIPs, and Subdeployments cascade-SKIPs
       transitively via its dependency on Deployments. ADR-010 v4 amendment
       (this sprint) records the 3-deep chain wiring. Sister cascade XML
       ops/test-results/sprint-ets-08-cascade-2026-04-30.xml VERIFIES the
       6-class cascade (5 SystemFeatures-level + 1 Deployments-transitive).
       GeoRobotix IUT state at sprint time: 1 deployment (16sp744ch58g) with
       empty subdeployments — IUT-state-honest SKIP applies for all 4 @Tests
       (HTTP 200 + items: [] empty pattern, per Sprint 7 PropertyDefinitions
       precedent). -->
  <!-- Sprint 9 S-ETS-09-01 (REQ-ETS-PART1-012): GeoJSON group added as a PARTIAL
       systems read-only subset. GeoJSON depends-on="systemfeatures" because the subset
       validates /systems GeoJSON encoding and must cascade-SKIP if SystemFeatures fails.
       This sprint intentionally leaves mediatype-write, relation-types, and non-system
       schema/mapping subrequirements open. -->
  <!-- Sprint 10 S-ETS-10-01 (REQ-ETS-PART1-013): SensorML group added as a PARTIAL
       systems read-only subset. SensorML depends-on="systemfeatures" because the subset
       validates system SensorML representations and must cascade-SKIP if SystemFeatures
       fails. This sprint intentionally leaves mediatype-write, relation-types,
       deployment/procedure/property schema/mapping, and full SensorML 3.0 schema
       validation open. -->
  <!-- Sprint 11 S-ETS-11-01 (REQ-ETS-PART1-009): AdvancedFiltering group added as a
       PARTIAL systems/common-resource read-only subset. AdvancedFiltering depends-on
       "systemfeatures" because the subset validates /systems query behavior and must
       cascade-SKIP if SystemFeatures fails. Current default smoke target does not
       declare /conf/advanced-filtering, so this class is declaration-gated and
       SKIP-honest until a declaring IUT is used. -->
  <!-- Sprint 12 S-ETS-12-01 (REQ-ETS-PART1-010): CreateReplaceDelete group added as a
       systems-only safety-gated subset. CreateReplaceDelete depends-on
       "systemfeatures" because it validates /systems mutation behavior and must
       cascade-SKIP if SystemFeatures fails. POST/PUT/DELETE are guarded by explicit
       mutation-tests-enabled=true plus mutation-iut-policy=dedicated-mutable-iut; the
       known public GeoRobotix IUT is hard-denied even if both parameters are set. -->
  <!-- Sprint 13 S-ETS-13-01 (REQ-ETS-PART1-011): Update group added as a
       systems-only PATCH safety-gated subset. Update depends-on
       "createreplacedelete" because OGC Part 1 Update requires Create/Replace/Delete
       and OGC API Features Part 4 Update. PATCH is guarded by the same explicit
       mutation-tests-enabled=true plus mutation-iut-policy=dedicated-mutable-iut
       controls; the known public GeoRobotix IUT is hard-denied even if both parameters
       are set. -->
  <!-- Sprint 20 S-ETS-20-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-001): Part 2 API Common group added as a
       read-only declaration-gated subset. It depends-on "core common" because Part 2
       API Common builds on the CS API Part 1 API Common requirements class and OGC API
       Common behavior already exercised by the Core/Common roots. GeoRobotix does not
       currently declare /conf/api-common, so this group SKIPs honestly on the default
       smoke IUT instead of treating undeclared Part 2 behavior as PASS evidence. -->
  <!-- Sprint 21 S-ETS-21-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-002): Part 2 Datastream group added as a
       read-only declaration-gated subset. It depends-on "core common" rather than
       "part2apicommon" so an IUT that declares /conf/datastream but omits
       /conf/api-common can still produce scoped endpoint evidence while full
       /conf/datastream closure remains prerequisite-incomplete. -->
  <!-- Sprint 22 S-ETS-22-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-003): Part 2 ControlStream group added as a
       read-only declaration-gated subset. It depends-on "core common" rather than
       "part2apicommon" so an IUT that declares /conf/controlstream but omits
       /conf/api-common can still produce scoped endpoint evidence while full
       /conf/controlstream closure remains prerequisite-incomplete. -->
  <!-- Sprint 23 S-ETS-23-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-004): Part 2 Feasibility group added as a
       declaration-gated, no-public-POST subset. It depends on "core common" for
       structural consistency; runtime checks keep /req/controlstream prerequisite
       honesty visible without depending on the part2controlstream group, so an
       undeclared /conf/feasibility class SKIPs before any IUT-bound feasibility POST. -->
  <!-- Sprint 24 S-ETS-24-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-005): Part 2 System Events group added as
       a read-only declaration-gated subset. It depends on "core common systemfeatures"
       so Part 1 System availability is structurally present; runtime checks still keep
       /req/api-common prerequisite honesty separate from scoped endpoint evidence. -->
  <!-- Sprint 25 S-ETS-25-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-006): Part 2 Advanced Filtering group
       added as a read-only declaration-gated subset. It depends on
       "core common systemfeatures" rather than Part2ApiCommon, Part 1 AdvancedFiltering,
       or Part 2 resource-class groups so exact /conf/advanced-filtering declaration
       and prerequisite-honesty SKIPs remain visible instead of being hidden by
       upstream cascade-SKIPs on the default GeoRobotix IUT. -->
  <!-- Sprint 26 S-ETS-26-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-007): Part 2 Create/Replace/Delete group
       added as a safety-gated subset. It depends on "core common systemfeatures" so
       foundational resources are available, but not on Part2ApiCommon or Part 2
       resource-class groups; runtime checks keep prerequisite honesty, OPTIONS-only
       readiness, unavailable endpoints, and public-IUT mutation denial visible. -->
  <!-- Sprint 27 S-ETS-27-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-008): Part 2 Update group added as a
       safety-gated PATCH subset. It depends on "core common systemfeatures" so
       foundational resources are available, but not on Part2ApiCommon, Part 1 Update,
       Part 2 Create/Replace/Delete, or resource-class groups; runtime checks keep
       CRD/Features4 prerequisites, Clause 15 condition gates, OPTIONS PATCH readiness,
       unavailable endpoints, schema-rejection honesty, and public-IUT mutation denial
       visible. -->
  <!-- Sprint 28 S-ETS-28-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-009): Part 2 JSON group added as a
       declaration-gated, read-only schema-validation subset. It depends on "core common"
       rather than Part2ApiCommon, resource-class groups, or SystemFeatures so exact
       /conf/json declaration, SWE prerequisite visibility, resource condition gates, and
       public-IUT no-mutation behavior remain runtime-visible. -->
  <!-- Sprint 29 S-ETS-29-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-010): Part 2 SWE Common JSON group
       added as a declaration-gated, read-only schema/media-validation subset. It
       depends on "core common" rather than Part2ApiCommon, resource-class groups, or
       SystemFeatures so exact /conf/swecommon-json declaration, SWE Encoding Rules
       prerequisite visibility, resource condition gates, and public-IUT no-mutation
       behavior remain runtime-visible. -->
  <!-- Sprint 30 S-ETS-30-01 (REQ-ETS-PART2-011): Part 2 SWE Common Text group
       added as a declaration-gated, read-only schema/media-validation subset. It
       depends on "core common" rather than Part2ApiCommon, resource-class groups, or
       SystemFeatures so exact /conf/swecommon-text declaration, SWE Text Encoding Rules
       prerequisite visibility, resource condition gates, exact application/swe+text
       evidence, and public-IUT no-mutation behavior remain runtime-visible. -->
  <test name="Conformance Classes - Core + SystemFeatures + Common + Subsystems + Procedures + Deployments + SamplingFeatures + PropertyDefinitions + Subdeployments + GeoJSON + SensorML + AdvancedFiltering + CreateReplaceDelete + Update + Part2ApiCommon + Part2Datastream + Part2ControlStream + Part2Feasibility + Part2SystemEvent + Part2AdvancedFiltering + Part2CreateReplaceDelete + Part2Update + Part2Json + Part2SweCommonJson + Part2SweCommonText (OGC 23-001 /conf/core, /conf/system, /conf/subsystem, /conf/procedure, /conf/deployment, /conf/sf, /conf/property, /conf/subdeployment, /conf/geojson, /conf/sensorml, /conf/advanced-filtering, /conf/create-replace-delete, /conf/update; OGC 23-002 /conf/api-common, /conf/datastream, /conf/controlstream, /conf/feasibility, /conf/system-event, /conf/advanced-filtering, /conf/create-replace-delete, /conf/update, /conf/json, /conf/swecommon-json, /conf/swecommon-text; OGC 19-072 /conf/common)">
    <groups>
      <dependencies>
        <group name="systemfeatures" depends-on="core"/>
        <group name="subsystems" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="procedures" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="deployments" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="samplingfeatures" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="propertydefinitions" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="subdeployments" depends-on="deployments"/>
        <group name="geojson" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="sensorml" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="advancedfiltering" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="createreplacedelete" depends-on="systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="update" depends-on="createreplacedelete"/>
        <group name="part2apicommon" depends-on="core common"/>
        <group name="part2datastream" depends-on="core common"/>
        <group name="part2controlstream" depends-on="core common"/>
        <group name="part2feasibility" depends-on="core common"/>
        <group name="part2systemevent" depends-on="core common systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="part2advancedfiltering" depends-on="core common systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="part2createreplacedelete" depends-on="core common systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="part2update" depends-on="core common systemfeatures"/>
        <group name="part2json" depends-on="core common"/>
        <group name="part2swecommonjson" depends-on="core common"/>
        <group name="part2swecommontext" depends-on="core common"/>
      </dependencies>
    </groups>
    <classes>
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.SuitePreconditions" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.core.LandingPageTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.core.ConformanceTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.core.ResourceShapeTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.systemfeatures.SystemFeaturesTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.common.CommonTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.subsystems.SubsystemsTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.procedures.ProceduresTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.deployments.DeploymentsTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.samplingfeatures.SamplingFeaturesTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.propertydefinitions.PropertyDefinitionsTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.subdeployments.SubdeploymentsTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.geojson.GeoJsonTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.sensorml.SensorMlTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.advancedfiltering.AdvancedFilteringTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.createreplacedelete.CreateReplaceDeleteTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.update.UpdateTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.apicommon.Part2ApiCommonTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.datastream.Part2DatastreamTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.controlstream.Part2ControlStreamTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.feasibility.Part2FeasibilityTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.systemevent.Part2SystemEventTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.advancedfiltering.Part2AdvancedFilteringTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.createreplacedelete.Part2CreateReplaceDeleteTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.update.Part2UpdateTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.json.Part2JsonTests" />
      <class name="org.opengis.cite.ogcapiconnectedsystems10.conformance.part2.swecommonjson.Part2SweCommonJsonTests" />
